  /cartridge/<name>/invoke endpoint; no client-side change was needed
  for the sunset migration.
"""

# ─── Panic-attack sweep 2026-04-25 ─────────────────────────────────────
[panic-attack-sweep]
date = "2026-04-25"
last-result = "pass-with-classified-false-positives"
findings = """
echidnabot:
  - 2 Critical (ProofDrift on proofs/coq/admitted_stub.v + proofs/lean/sorry_stub.lean)
    → INTENTIONAL DOGFOOD FIXTURES from commit ec25aae. Designed to
      exercise the bot's failure path. False positives — panic-attack
      lacks fixture-exclusion; structural-first per memory rule but
      no config option exists. Not chasing.
  - 1 Low (MutationGap — no cargo-mutants config). Add later if mutation
    testing becomes an estate-wide rule.
  - Statistics: 17 unwrap_calls, 0 panic_sites, 15 unsafe_blocks (all
    legitimate FFI), 14 threading constructs.

vcl-ut:
  - 2 Critical (UnboundedAllocation on src/interface/{fmt,lint}/src/main.rs)
    → fs::read_to_string of operator-supplied file. CLI tools, trusted
      input. False positive in this context (no untrusted-input boundary).
  - 1 Medium (InsecureProtocol on echidna-client lib.rs)
    → http://127.0.0.1:8000 as the default echidna URL. Localhost; HTTPS
      isn't expected for default local-dev path. False positive.
  - 1 Low (MutationGap).

boj-server cartridges/echidna-llm-mcp:
  - 1 High (UnsafeCode on ffi/cartridge_shim.zig)
    → 1 unsafe @ptrCast in the FFI shim. Per memory rule "panic-attack
      unsafe_blocks conflates banned partial casts with legitimate FFI
      try/catch — classify each hit." This one is legitimate FFI surface.
  - 1 Medium (InsecureProtocol on mod.js)
    → localhost echidna URL. False positive (same as vcl-ut).

echidna:
  - SCAN TIMED OUT at 180s (repo too large for a single assail run).
    Defer to a chunked/per-subdir invocation in a future sweep.

Real critical findings: 0. All flagged criticals are classified
false-positives or operator-trusted-input patterns.
"""
